name: Bramble Cabin
description:
Welcome to Bramble Cabin, just 15 minutes from St Andrews . The hobby farm is powered by wind & solar & built by hand. Until recently thefarm was off-grid. The cabin is cozy, located near the main farmhouse and has all its own amenities, including a composting toilet, shower, propane stove and a view of the barn and pasture.

Wilber, the donkey sadly passed away this winter. The sheep are more timid but so enjoyable to observe out in the pasture, and may wander over to say hello’
neighborhood_overview: Situated on the tidal Bocabec River, Bramble Cabin is just fifteen minutes drive from St. Andrews or St George, 30  minutes to the Grand Manan Ferry, and 50 minutes to Saint John. This peaceful corner of New Brunswick is teeming with wildlife, lots of wonderful hiking trails nearby (including on-site) and is the perfect location to relax.

name: A little piece of heaven with step in water access
description: welcome to my little paradise on Harvey Lake. My home is complete with everything for your stay at the lake. You’ll be able to watch fire stick tv when not staring at the lake, log onto wifi to post pics, cook on the bbq, sit out on the deck and let the time go by, fresh linens, so all you have to bring is your food, drinks, your own toiletries to have a good time. Please read all sections for more information about your stay.
neighborhood_overview: Your next getaway is located on a dead end road on the backside of Harvey lake. A slow rural road with not much traffic which is good for children and walkers. A short ten minute drive from the village of Harvey which contains everything you need for your stay just in case you run out.
host_about: Hey everyone. Welcome to my little piece of paradise on Harvey Lake. My name is Rob Swan and I’m happy to share my place here on the water with you. Born and raised here is Harvey, I was very happy to move back here and call Harvey my home once again. I work full time but I am happy to share the lake experience with you because I feel that if you sit on my deck on a nice quiet morning, the ducks swimming by, maybe one of my neighbours in their kayak, it gives you piece of mind and changes you in a good way. When not working you will find me curling around the world through, Curling Across the Nation. This has allowed me to visit places around the world I never thought I would and that’s what my place on the lake offers you, a chance to get away. One step off my deck and you are in the lake, unlike other places on the lake that offer “lake access” that forces you to walk through someone’s yard or deck to get into the lake. So do not settle for less when booking your getaway. Harvey lake offer a great fishing experience, kayaking, swimming, leisure boating, and in the village(a short 10 minute drive) you’ll find a gas station, a pizza shop, several local restaurants, several local country stores, a liquor outlet, and so much more to serve your needs during your stay. My house offer sat TV, wireless, washer/dryer, dishwasher, bbq, lawn chairs, so everything you need for a great experience at the lake. For more information, just ask. O I

name: Down the Road Guesthouse
description:
Welcome to Down the Road Guesthouse, your perfect base for exploring the Bay of Fundy’s highest tides in the world.

Located just minutes from the Rocks Provincial Park, our historic five bedroom, two bath home has been in our family for more than 150 years, longer than Canada has been a country. It was completely renovated in 2017 while keeping the country character of the home. All prices include tax.
neighborhood_overview:
The best part of the area is that it sits between two beautiful nature parks. The Hopewell Rocks Provincial Park is just a few minutes away while Fundy National Park is about a half-hour down a scenic country highway.

For outdoor lovers, hiking, swimming, zip lining, kayaking and some of the most dramatic views on Canada’s east coast are just around the corner.

There are also several small museums in the area including a historic jail and courthouse.

Moncton, the hub of Canada’s Maritime region, is a short drive away, with an international airport, fine dining and some of the best shopping in the Atlantic region.

The nearby Village of Hillsborough features a small selection of groceries, gas, and restaurants, while Alma, (30 km or 18 miles away) is the gateway to Fundy Park, with some of the best seafood our region has to offer. This is another great spot to see the power of tides.

name: Swallow View Cottage - lovely lighthouse views!
description: Swallow View Cottage is a beautiful spot to experience Atlantic Canadian island life on Grand Manan. Less than 5 minute walk to the beach, views of the historic Swallowtail lighthouse and gorgeous sunrises from the house, a minute drive from the ferry - you'll be very comfortable in this mid-19th century home.
neighborhood_overview: Dead end road so traffic isn't too crazy here! Well, let's be honest it's Grand Manan - "crazy" traffic is defined as like 3 cars in a row.
host_about:
I have lived on Grand Manan for 5 years now after falling in love with the island and its way of life. I'm originally from Quispamsis, NB and have also spent time living in various places in Ontario. I'm a teacher at Grand Manan Community School  and adore my job and my students. Once you take the drive from the house to the school, you'll understand how it is easy to fall in love with island life.

During the summers I like to travel to visit family and thought it would be a shame if the house was empty during such a beautiful time on the island - so here we are! I purchased the house in the fall of 2017 and have been busily renovating it to make it even cozier to welcome guests this summer. I'm happy to help you plan your vacation to New Brunswick, don't hesitate to ask for ideas/thoughts/suggestions in Grand Manan and anywhere else in the province your vacation may take you!

Two wineries within easy drives.  Or just sit on the porch in a rocker.

description:
Beautiful large 3 bedroom house on the secluded waterfront on 5 acres of land in Petite-Lamèque, NB. Ideal place to make the beach, relax, enjoy nature, watch the breathtaking sunsets and do sports like kitesurfing, windsurfing, SUP, etc. on the ground itself. Surrounded by conifers and bordered by the sea, my residence is an exceptional and unique site not to be missed.

3-4 nights minimum depending on dates
Discount 1 week +
neighborhood_overview:
This property is among the most popular kitesurfing and windsurfing sites. Few people are allowed to practice these sports from this site. There are two sides to the site: the Baie des Chaleurs and the spot called "the pool" where the water is mirror and shallow. From beginner to expert, the favorable winds are from the southwest, west and northwest.

*** The rental of this house is not available for sailing schools. Only the Kite Académie school have access to the site to operate.

We have wonderfully quiet, lovely neighbors where everyone seems to look out for others, a very safe neighborhood!

But, expect the unexpected, in the case of an emergency the RCMP are around the corner and the medical clinic and veterinary hospital are 3 minutes away.
host_about:
Hi everyone!! I'm 68, a mom of two, (our daughter lives nearby and our son is in Montreal with his lovely British wife, Rosie) and  "NanNan" of 2, of course beautiful grandchildren.  I've been with my partner for 46 years,  love yoga, meditating, vegan lifestyle, the beach, exercising, tai chi, walking, especially in nature, Qi gong, reading, biking and travelling.  And on that list should be the love my 4 legged fur family as well, from guinea pigs to rabbits to Theodore, Teddy, our pot bellied pig, to a tamed "wild" Starling, (who would sit on the backs of one of our dogs when out walking) to all our dogs and cats over the years.  I grew up with a spider monkey in the 60's (he came from Florida).  Mickey, would wear diapers we would make out of towels and I, as a teenager, would dress him up. We would take him out to stores and he would hold our hands and just walk beside us.  A very good boy!!!! He loved TV and breakfast was his favorite, sitting with us at the table eating his favorite-toast with jam and orange juice, like he was another sibling!!

Have worked as a medical secretary, civil engineering technologist, fitness trainer, yoga instructor and in nursing.  But that part of my life is secondary to the love of my family. That is my legacy! we tavelled for several years until the g'babies came along and now can't be too far from them.  

Have used AirBNB personally and loved each home/apt we entered.  Now we are moving closer to take care of our g'babies, but can't let go of our beach house, so we decided to open our home to other beach lovers!! YOU!! Enjoy!!!!

description:
Nestled by the iconic Sea Caves, a short drive leads you to the breathtaking Fundy Trail Provincial Park. Embrace outdoor adventures with hiking, kayaking, and the unique experience of exploring the ocean floor during low tide.
Conveniently, the beach and restaurants are a mere 2-minute walk away. Built in the 1880s, this house exudes charm with its wide wooden floorboards and plaster walls upstairs—a timeless retreat for those seeking a touch of history and coastal allure.
neighborhood_overview:
Discover proximity to the sea caves, a variety of restaurants, and a quick drive to the scenic Fundy Trail Provincial Park. Nestled in a serene neighborhood, you'll experience tranquility, although distant sounds from the sea caves and restaurants add a unique ambiance. Enjoy the best of both worlds—a private location in a quiet setting while being close to everything. Note that, come October, many local restaurants take a seasonal pause, enhancing the peaceful atmosphere of the area.

Exciting news! We are proud owners of the Blue Whale cottage next door and the captivating lighthouse cottage perched on the hill. Whether you choose the coastal charm of the Blue Whale or the elevated retreat at the lighthouse, both properties offer unique experiences while ensuring your comfort and enjoyment. We look forward to hosting you in these neighboring havens.
host_about:
I’m a teacher and now own three cottages!  The lighthouse cottage was a dream that just recently came to fruition.  I still can’t believe it!

Owning a cottage in St. Martins has always been a dream of mine and I can’t believe how popular they have become.   I have been coming here since I was a child, and been a full-time resident in the summertime since 2013.

name: Beach Glass House
description: Beach Glass House is situated in the village of North Head on Grand Manan.  It faces the idyllic Stanley Beach, the iconic Swallowtail Lighthouse, and the bustling wharves of both the ferry and local fishermen. A short walk down the lane deposits you on to Stanley Beach. Enjoy relaxation in a friendly, convenient, and serene location. You won't want to leave!
neighborhood_overview: Your stay at Beach Glass House is a quintessential Grand Manan experience.  Wake up in the morning with your coffee on the deck and observe as the fishermen leave the North Head Wharf for their long days at sea.  Tell time throughout the day by the comings and goings of the Grand Manan ferries.  For breakfast journey up to the North Head Bakery for fresh French pastries, the best on the island (open in late June-October). Watch as the Bay of Fundy molds the landscape every 6 hours with the world's largest tidal fluctuations. You can take all of this in while walking Stanley Beach, combing the sand for a variety of ocean treasures and its bounty of sea glass.  Bring your kayaks and launch from Stanley Beach to enjoy some of the hidden spots on Grand Manan.  A menagerie of birds call this island home waiting for you to spot them. At night, watch Swallowtail Lighthouse call the fishermen home.  Post Office Pizza, Convenience/Drug store, children's park, hospital, local shops, hiking, chur

name: The Johnville Guest House - lovely, private, safe
description: The Johnville Guest House is a renovated home in the heart of the rural hills of Johnville New Brunswick.  Just 4 km from the beautiful St. John River Valley, the Guest House is a perfect location for a relaxing stay away from the city.  Main floor includes fully equipped kitchen, open concept dining/living room, main bedroom, full bath and laundry.  Second floor has a second bedroom (2 twin beds or 1 king), a spacious separate living area with pull out couch and a 1/2 bath. A lovely, safe haven
neighborhood_overview: We are directly across from the Johnville Labyrinth and Fairy Path and are close to trails for hiking or bicycling in summer and snow shoeing and cross country skiing in winter.  There are several downhill ski facilities within driving distance (Mars Hill Maine, Crabbe Mountain, Mount Farlagne not far off ) and golf clubs (Hartland, Mars Hills Maine, Aroostock Valley, Woodstock, Grand Falls).  Snow mobile trails are also easily accessible.  There are several art galleries (the Andrew & Laura McCain Gallery in Florenceville-Bristol is under 15 minutes away as well as Creek Village Gallery and Cafe in Woodstock and Acanthus Gallery in Grand Falls).  There is a local farmers' market every Thursday in the summer in Florenceville-Bristol.  There is also the River Bend Balloon Festival in Bath every long weekend in September for those who wish to try hot air ballooning or just take in the majesty of the balloons floating along the river valley. name: Country Charm in Shannon, NB
description: This house was built in 1910 by the Jones Family in Shannon.  The house maintains a lot of its original charm, with wood wainscotting and cedar shingle finish.   It is located within walking distance of the farm and the Jones Mill Falls, which makes a great swimming hole in the Summer time.  At the farm, help with the chores such as feeding a calf.  You can also fish in our u-fish lake for speckled trout, hike the trails or paddle around the lake in a canoe.
neighborhood_overview: We are close to the Washademoak Lake for boaters in the summer time.  We are also centrally located between Saint John, Moncton and Fredericton, about an hours drive from each.

name: Gorgeous Beachfront Getaway
description: Our Gorgeous Beachfront Getaway is a newly-renovated dream home with an open-concept living room, dining and kitchen area, a large bathroom, and two bedrooms that each have a queen-size bed. We are located on an expansive property that leads to Stanley Beach, the perfect spot for strolling, sunbathing and collecting beach glass.
neighborhood_overview: Within a fifteen-minute walk from our home, you'll find many attractions, seasonal businesses and amenities, such as the fishermen's and ferry wharves, a cafe and several dining options, gift shops, kayak tours, bakery and convenience store. The Hole in the Wall rock formation is nearby, as well as the spectacular Swallowtail Lighthouse, Long Eddy (the Whistle) Lighthouse, and many of the island's well-maintained hiking trails.
host_about: I'm an avid traveller and adventurer, and I love discovering new places and introducing visitors to my home island.

description: Every detail will make your stay easy and comfortable.  All natural bedding washed in unscented laundry soap.  IQAir purifier on the main floor. Along the river trail you will be close to the Ganong Chocolate Museum and Chocolatier as well as restaurants with waterview outdoor dining.  Nearby the Garcelon Civic Center has an ice arena, fitness centre, and aquatic center with two pools, one slide and a dry sauna.

name: Beautiful Downtown 3BR Classic Century Home!
description: Welcome to Odell Avenue or should I say 'Oh WOW' Avenue!!  This pristine property backs up onto beautiful Wilmot Park and is only minutes to downtown on foot. The kitchen is newly renovated and is a great spot for gathering.  If you prefer to take dinner outside on a nice evening the front porch has you covered!   The living room and 2 bedrooms feature 50" HD Smart TVs to cover all of your entertainment needs.  You will love this spacious 3 bedroom house for your next Fredericton getaway!!
neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood in the 'gardens' of Fredericton is a great location.  Call me bias, but it is the best area of the city!! Only minutes away from the walking/biking trails parallel to the Saint John River or the restaurants downtown.  You have Fredericton's heartbeat right at your back doorstep and parks galore at your front doorstep!  Across  the street (and I mean literally across the street!) you'll find a splash pad, tennis courts, playground, lawn bowling, and plenty of green space for however you want to spend your time.  A block away, at the other end of Rookwood Avenue awaits O'dell Park!  Here you can picnic, play frisbee golf, mountain bike,  jog, walk, snow shoe, or even cross country ski throughout the many trails the park has to offer.  This area is a gem in Fredericton in what it offers and I encourage you to take advantage!

name: Stylish, modern home next to beach - Cap Pelé area
description:
Betty's by the Beach is a 3-minute walk from the beautiful Atlantic ocean. The beach is clean and you can swim (if you're staying in the summer!). This 4-season getaway home is located in a quiet, well-maintained area.

Why Betty's on the Beach? This home is named after my grandma, who was known for hosting people. She always had something warm and generous to say. I think you'll find that warm vibe here.

Plus all of the amenities you need: fully equipped kitchen, fibre op internet, cable
neighborhood_overview:
Betty's by the Beach is your ideal getaway location to unwind. We have fast wifi and cable if you want them, though there's also plenty of nature to enjoy. You can bike along the quiet streets, head to the beach or lounge at the house or in the screened-in gazebo.

If you need 'staples', we're a quick 10 minute drive away from:

- the Fresh Mart grocery store
- 2 bakeries
- fish markets, if you want to try local fish (!)
- the l'Aboiteau wharf and beach
- Tim Hortons
- NB liquor store inside the Irving
- multiple gas stations
host_about: I'm an east coast entrepreneur who loves both hosting and travelling.  I've travelled to five continents, and the thing I'm always looking for is a sense of community and wonder.

name: Painter's Paradise - Gypsy June's Island Cottage
description: Gypsy June's Island cottage is located  just a 4 minute drive from the ferry.  Just minutes from Stanley's Beach, one of the best beaches on the Island, and across the road from the best Bakery this side of Montreal.!! Your stay at Gypsy June's can be an unplugged visit to the painter's paradise of Grand Manan, or you can take advantage of the wifi to stay in touch on your travels! Longer stays are preferred, but you are welcome to message if you want to request a stay of a shorter duration.
neighborhood_overview: Gypsy June's Island cottage is located across from the best Bakery this side of Montreal, short walk/bike ride or drive to Corner Store, which is also home to the local Drug Store. Just minutes from one of the best beaches on the Island {Stanley's]. New York style pizza at {Post office Pizza} and a fabulous coffee shop [The Old Well House] that serves coffees; fine dining at the Inn at Whale Cove and much more!
host_about:
When having the opportunity to purchase my Aunt and Uncle's property, in sunny North Head,I jumped at the opportunity (Website hidden by Airbnb) being it was in the same neighborhood as my Grandparent's home had been....where the hospital now sits.
I was living in Alberta at the time, and envisioned summers relaxing on the beaches and exploring old childhood haunts. . Recently retired, Life has changed, giving me time to focus on what the next chapter brings. .
I very much enjoy sharing my love of Grand Manan with guests coming to stay and enjoying all of what this magical place has to offer.(Website hidden by Airbnb)Grand  Manan has changed somewhat, from my childhood days, and is becoming a vacationers paradise. Relax, enjoy and breathe in the experience. You won't be disappointed .We haven't been voted as one of the Top 10 Small Island's in the World by mistake. LGBTQ+ friendly. Bon Vacation.

description:
Where the road ends and your journey begins.
This beautiful spot is located nestled on the banks of the Miramichi river about 1km off Route 8 . Perfect location for winter, spring, summer and fall activities. You will feel right at home in this private locate. A great spot to reconnect, de-stress and recharge .

This space is an ideal spot to get away and recharge or a perfect location to do outdoor activities all year round.

Bring your snowshoes or cross country skis and see the property from a different perspective.
If you are lucky you may see some of the locate deer.

Stunning 4 bedroom , 1 bathroom private home on sprawling 3 acre property with your own Bay of Fundy cliff side lookout.
Just steps from incredible secluded Browns Beach , 2kms to picturesque West Quaco Lighthouse and only 4 to 5 kms to restaurants , shops , the harbor and the famous St. Martins Sea Caves.

host_about:
Hello , I am Pat and I love St. Martins and the Bay of Fundy. 
I manage several incredible vacation homes here  in St. Martins and West Quaco.
I manage...
Authentic Bay of Fundy Beachside Home ,Waters Edge Bay of Fundy, Rosehill Cottage by the Sea Caves and Homestead -Gateway to the Fundy Trail.
I also opperate a custom Woodworking store - Authentic Bay of Fundy store/studio specializing in one of a kind charcuterie boards and Laser engraving located at 15 Beach Street.
We are excited to share the incredible village of St. Martins with our guests and hope to provide the ideal vacation experience.

We understand the variety of vacation styles that may appeal to different groups and hope to provide the best experience to suit each groups needs.

We plan to offer our guests all the privacy wanted when renting a vacation home or cottage but we also want to be available for any information , recommendations or to help arrange the perfect excursions or personalised souvenirs/gifts.. so feel free to reach out to me.
We look forward to having you as our guests here in beautiful St. Martins New Brunswick.

name: Home with a spectacular view!
description:
Our old family homestead is waiting for you! From the wrap-around veranda, enjoy a "Million Dollar View" of the majestic expanse of the Shepody Marshes, Mary's Point Bird Sanctuary and Grindstone Island. Nicely located in rural NB, just 10 km from the Hopewell Rocks, 24 km from Cape Enrage, 13 km from Shepody National Wildlife area (Mary's Point), and 32 km to Fundy National Park.
Saw Mill Creek Covered Bridge and walking trails are just a minute away.
neighborhood_overview:
Bring your kayaks and bikes to this destination because both opportunities are a hop, skip, and jump away!
A family style restaurant (including seafood! and gluten free meals) is a short 5 minute drive away.
Liquor store, pharmacy, gas station with take out meals are within a 5 minute drive.
This property is located within 10 minutes of the world famous Hopewell Rocks where you can explore the ocean floor by foot at low tide and by kayak at high tide.
Fundy National Parks offers dozens of hiking trails, beaches and a beautiful golf course.
The village of Alma, outside Fundy National Park, has shops, restaurants, a micro brewery and fresh lobster direct from the fisherman (seasonally).
Cape Enrage with its beautiful lighthouse and fog horn dating back to 1838 offers adventures including rapelling, zip-lining, obstacle course and a beach walk at low tide.
host_about: We are sisters who proudly have a 6th generation connection to this part of Albert County, New Brunswick.  We love this area and are so proud of it.  We welcome you to enjoy it as much as we do (Website hidden by Airbnb)

description:

neighborhood_overview:

host_about:
55 yrs male working in film animation.

I am Irish, originally from the Beautiful City of  Dublin. 

I love to play music, sing, write and record music at home,  with the occasional live performance.  

I currently live between London UK and Canada. I have also lived in Scotland, France, Argentina, and Brazil. 

I am an avid traveller and do so about 3/4 times a year. My favourite cities right now are Istanbul, Barcelona and Buenos Aires. 
Cities are really my thing, the buzz, the people, the aromas, the food, the architecture.

I am pretty laid back and easy going and get along with most people easily. 
I'm also old enough to be responsible, but still love to let myself go and enjoy good, food, drinks, and have a laugh with friends, both old and new.

Other things i enjoy.
Stand Up Comedy, Museums, Theatre, Concerts and all sorts of live performance. I also love to watch movies, particularly foreign language, drama, suspense and thrillers. 

But enough about me, what's you story?

name: The Shorebird - ocean views & beach - St Andrews
description: Enjoy panoramic ocean views from a contemporary waterfront home. Wake up with the sunrise over Passamaquoddy Bay (Bay of Fundy). Our neighbourhood is quiet, with mostly permanent residents on large lots around Passamaquoddy Bay. There is a public road that goes down to the beach next to the property.

We would love to make sure you have all the info you need to have the vacation experience that is right for you.
host_about:
I spend my time chasing around my two little girls with my husband, Justin. I grew up in Northern Ontario, surrounded by a New Brunswick marketing campaign carefully overseen by my Fredericton parents. Posters, art, music - even little figurines of Saint Andrews, where Justin and I are hosts. 

We spent every family vacation on the east coast & now I get to do the same with my daughters. In between, we hope you enjoy our home.

host_about:

While living in Arizona my husband and I decided to build a home on the island so we could enjoy island summers and escape the desert heat. -Cheers

Treena

name: Waterfront 92 Front St Gagetown, NB Vacation Spot
description: 92 Front St. Waterfront Vacation Spot in the village of Gagetown on the beautiful Saint John River.  This newly renovated "above the garage" apartment is very private with an extensive list of  amenities for your comfort and a gorgeous view! Bring your boat the public park next door offers a boat launch access a public park, & free parking for your boat trailer.  Come explore our river our artisan village, an incredible outdoor experience boating, fishing, sailing, kayaking, swimming & biking!
neighborhood_overview:
Gagetown is a beautiful quaint village on the Saint John River. It is safe, people are friendly and you can walk anywhere in the village. The village of Gagetown has a long history of artisans with skilled and beautifully designed pottery, paintings, weavers, fibre artists, galleries with artisans work for sale. Gagetown also has a Marina and wharf that hosts travellers and sells gas for travelling along the river. The Old Boot Pub has a famous history for quenching the thirst of travellers along the way both inside the pub or on the outdoor deck enjoying the scenic river and lovely boats passing by and enjoying the local activities. Golivers restaurant hosts weddings, various functions and fine dining. Creek View Restaurant also have lovely food and sits on the crest of Tilley road overlooking the river.
Gagetown also has a lovely Sunday market that opens at 11:00am and runs to 3:00 there you will find everything from beautiful food, coffee, preserves, wood working, potter
host_about: Hi I am an interior designer and my husband is a renovator that makes all my design details evolve into beautiful space. We have two lovely black Labradors and we all love to spend time in this beautiful space on the water!

Located in a small, rural Village, quiet side street. The house feels very private although there are friendly neighbour's. A cozy front porch, backyard with picnic table, mature trees, bushes and flowers surround the property.

Nearby are so many beaches and hiking, Caledonia Mountain Gorge, Shepody National Wildlife Preserve and Mary's Point, Cape Enrage and the Fundy National Park and village of Alma are a short drive. The world famous Hopewell Rocks are a short drive as well.

There is access to a water fall, backcountry camping and two lookouts, and picnic area walking distance from the house as well as boat launch. Currently there is a weekly market around the corner which features local food, artisans and farm gate opportunities.

name: Serenity By The Sea: The Coleman Cottage
description:
Looking for a cozy place to stay this spring and summer with all the amenities?

We have it here!

We are located in downtown Alma; walking distance to all the restaurants, shops, grocery store. We are only steps away from the beach featuring the tides of the Bay of Fundy and the beautiful Fundy National Park.

There is so much to do, hiking, biking, boating, and more to fill those beautiful sunny days.

For Pet Policy, fees and expectations, please go to "Other Details to Note"
neighborhood_overview:
The cottage was originally built in 1884 and was located in Point Wolfe in Fundy Park. It arrived at its present location on a barge that floated down the bay. Today it is located along the Upper Salmon River which is fed by the Bay of Fundy as the tide comes in right in downtown Alma. There are lots of homes/cottages/restaurants etc in the immediate area, and you are only seconds away from the entry to Fundy Park. You will need a park pass if you plan to enjoy all the park has to offer - In the summer, you have the pool, lakes, biking, hiking, fishing and exploring! In the winter months you will find our location at the base of the snow mobile trail on one end of the street and the gas station/corner store on the other end. name: Union House
description:
Union House is our family home, as we split our time between two cities. We love the open concept and the kitchen bar where large and little ones can tuck up for a snack or a chat. The living room is like one big pillow (with TV attached). There's a cupboard full of games, art supplies, and books for all ages.

At Union House, we have tried to make it most everything you would need to have a proper staycation. Cozy, bright, and beautiful is why we love it; we think you will too :)
neighborhood_overview:
Centrally located, Union House is a 5 minute walk from downtown shops, the 5 Kings craft restaurant and brewhouse, and the Garcelon indoor public pool (and sauna!).

We are also a 5 minute walk from the Elm Street nature park and Dover Hill park, both offering wonderful hikes in river valleys, with stunning views of the St Croix rapids. There is also a lovely river walk which starts behind Something's Brewing Cafe.

Don't hesitate to ask us for recommendations on hikes, beaches, and restaurants outside of St. Stephen as well. We know all the swimming holes and sand beaches, as well as the best spots for fish and chips. The resort town of St. Andrews by the Sea is a gorgeous 20 minute drive away, as you follow the St. Croix river from St. Stephen out to the Fundy Bay, where St. Andrews is perched on the end of a peninsula.
host_about: I'm a life partner and a father of 3 boys. I'm a researcher and a writer and an artist.

name: Hillside Hideaway at Parlee
description:
Relax with your family at this waterfront retreat. Enjoy a week at the beach or a comfy home-base to explore the east coast. With a fresh facelift in 2022 and creature comforts for adults and kids alike, we hope you enjoy the area as much as we do!

Rentals Sat-Sat in July and August. Flexible off season.

Rated one of Canada’s top 5 beaches by lonely planet in 2022. Parlee is uniquely positioned to be the warmest beach on Canada’s Atlantic coast.
neighborhood_overview:
The cottage is an 8 minute walk to the beach at the end of Fernwood Ave.

The public beach is part of the Provincial Park and boasts playgrounds, restaurants, event venues/live music, change rooms/washrooms/showers and volleyball courts. There are multiple walking and biking trails throughout.

The private (outside the provincial park) beach is enjoyed by cottagers and locals and is dog-friendly.

The town of Shediac is a 5 minute drive and boasts many art galleries, gift shops and a wide variety of restaurants including family friendly and fine dining options. There is a drive-in theater close by and bowling lanes for any rainy days.

Shediac has several grocery stores (IGA, Sobeys, No Frills), NB Liquor and a medical clinic.

name: Coastal Charm - Rustic 3BR -20mins to Parlee Beach
description:
Welcome to our peaceful cottage retreat in Pointe-du-Chêne! We're nestled in a cute cottage town. It's a 3-minute walk to the neighbourhood beach and coastline, and a 20-minute walk to Parlee Beach where locals love to go swimming and fish in the summer season.

Our cottage offers a cozy living room with plenty of natural light and a small reading nook, a fully-equipped kitchen, 3 bedrooms each with a queen-size bed, and back patio complete with dining table and seating around a fire pit.
neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to this amazing home located in the heart of New Brunswick which is located in a picturesque and charming neighborhood, offering the perfect blend of natural beauty and modern conveniences!

Nestled along the coast of the Northumberland Strait, Pointe-du-Chêne is a quaint fishing village that offers a unique taste of maritime life. You'll find a variety of fresh seafood restaurants, artisanal shops, and local attractions within walking distance of this cozy property.

The neighbourhood is also home to several stunning beaches, including the popular Parlee Beach Provincial Park. The park offers a sandy beach, as well as a variety of recreational activities such as swimming, boating, and beach volleyball.

Beyond the beach, Pointe-du-Chêne is also conveniently located near a number of other popular attractions in the area, including the famous Shediac Lobster Festival and the Irving Eco-Centre.

Hello,

We’re Brett & Katie, happily married and proud parents of the cutest seven year old!

Brett & Katie

neighborhood_overview:
Parlee Beach: Located within a 5-minute walking distance, Parlee Beach is a must-visit destination. With its pristine sandy beaches and warm waters, it's an ideal spot for swimming, sunbathing, and beachside picnics. Enjoy beach volleyball, build sandcastles, or take a leisurely stroll along the shoreline. The beach also offers amenities like changing rooms, washrooms, and a canteen for your convenience!

The Point-du-Chene Wharf and Restaurants: Located near Parlee Beach, within a 5-minute walking distance the Wharf is a charming waterfront area bustling with activity. Explore a variety of local restaurants that serve up delicious seafood dishes, from freshly caught lobster and oysters to mouthwatering fish and chips. Enjoy picturesque views of the marina as you savour your meal. While we do our absolute best to keep as many of these away from our property as possible, nature rules in the countryside.

The Champlain Place Mall is a central public transportation hub. The buses can take you to Université de Moncton or NBCC in 10 mins!

Welcome to this charming neighbourhood in Dieppe! This quiet and peaceful cul-de-sac offers a tranquil escape from the hustle and bustle of city life, while still being conveniently located near all the amenities you need.

Take a stroll along the tree-lined streets and enjoy the beauty of the well-maintained gardens and lawns. Stroll around Dieppe Market, or head over to Dieppe Rotary Park or Irishtown Nature Park. For those who enjoy outdoor activities, you could also visit the Magnetic Hill Zoo or explore the history of the area at the New Brunswick Aviation Museum or the Dieppe Military Museum.

The neighborhood is also home to several great restaurants and cafes, where you can enjoy a delicious meal or a refreshing drink. With its perfect balance of serenity and convenience, this is the ideal destination for your next getaway!

The salt marsh interpretation center of the Baie des Chaleur and the municipal beach are a must-see for those who want to get to know the area better. description: Your whole group will enjoy easy access to everything from this upper level two bedroom unit located in a family friendly centrally located home.  Two generously sized bedrooms with smart TVs and queen beds offer a comfortable nights rest. The main living area features vaulted ceilings, a 50” Smart TV, a separate desk for working and a fireplace for ambiance (not functioning).
neighborhood_overview: Centrally located in a family friendly neighbourhood known locally at Sunshine Gardens.  You’re just minutes from the downtown core on the south side of Fredericton (30 minutes if you’re walking) but surrounded by a quiet family neighbourhood without the hustle and bustle.  Within walking distance is Wilmot Park which offers, tennis, and basket ball courts as well as lawn bowling. For children there is also a Splash Pad to cool down during the warmer months as well as a play ground. Odell Park is also within a five minute walk and offers 400 acres of land featuring a duck pond, botanical gardens, the Odell Lodge and many kilometres of trails to enjoy nature. All other amenities are near by including restaurants, shopping, grocery/convenience stores, and gas stations.

Ideal for Travel Nurses
This modern, spacious, clean, bright and beautifully decorated home is located in a great area of ​​Moncton/New Brunswick.
The house has 4 bedrooms, 2 full bathrooms, closed garage for one car, EV charging station inside the garage, driveway for 2 more cars, cozy solarium, 2 spacious family rooms with TV and fireplace in each of them.
Construction/renovation was finalized in October/2023.
Everything is new in the house.
High end appliances and furniture.
neighborhood_overview:
Grove Hamlet subdivision is located in the Moncton city lines, this tightly knit bilingual community is able to access highways and the heart of Dieppe & Downtown Moncton effortlessly.

This area is well suited for young professionals and young families.

The neighborhood is close to both francophone & anglophone schools as well as numerous daycares. With walking trails accessible in the entire area and the KAY arena close by, the Groove Hamlet subdivision can very well support a healthy and active lifestyle that includes skating, walking and much more.

name: Secluded, spectacular view w/hot tub & firepit!
description:
Romantic getaway, near St. Andrew's, Canada's #1 tourist destination!
This secluded luxury accommodation w/ hot tub & firepit, on the water has 38 foot tides!

Access to a table reserved for SEAWINDS guests every Saturday night at the Rossmount, one of Canada's top 10 restaurants! ( Difficult to get reservations in the summer.)

SEAWINDS- queen bed w/remote, mini fridge, Kureig, microwave, air-conditioning, safe to drink well water,
4K TV & the most spectacular view!
Even seals & porpoises
neighborhood_overview:
Very private area with a beautiful view.

Great place to use a base to visit all the local festivals and communities, including famous
St. Andrews by the Sea, only 20 min. away!

Walking distance to the 350 acre Ganong Nature Park, approximately 10 min.


SEAWINDS is located at the estuary where the sea waters of the Bay of Fundy meet the St. Croix River.
You will enjoy viewing the 38 foot tides coming and going from your private deck.
Twice a day, 160 billion tons of seawater is pulled into the world famous Bay of Fundy.
More than 4 times the combined flow of fresh water rivers on the planet is forced into a tighter and shallower area as the bay narrows.

You can use the private stairway that takes you to the beach and walk the ocean floor at low tide!

Many excellent choices from Picaroons Pub to gourmet, fine dining!

As a special courtesy to my guests, reservations have been made every Saturday
host_about:
This beautiful self- contained studio can be your hideaway when it is closed as a yoga studio.
If the weather allows you can inquire about a private yoga class on the 16'x36' deck.
Private entrance, closet, bathroom with shower. One large room with a wall of windows/garden door onto the deck overlooking the historic St. Croix River, which serves as an international boundary. 
Furnished with table and chairs,  leather couch, coffee table, table that can be used as a desk, makeup table with 20X magnification mirror, Wi-Fi, 4 K TV with satellite, DVD player, mini fridge, microwave, Kureig, queen size bed with remote to raise/lower foot of bed, new mattress topped with 4" memory foam!
You will enjoy the spectacular view of the  US coastline, including famous St Croix Island where the first settlers, led by Samuel de Champlain landed in 1604.
You are 20 minutes from the No. 1 rated destination in Canada, St. Andrews by the Sea!
If you like seafood, as much as I do, I can share the best places to buy fresh!

This area is known for great dining, including one of Canada's top 10 restaurants, Rossmount!

Please  note:
Be ready to chill this is a... 
NO STRESS ZONE  :)

name: By the Sea - Paradise secluded w/hot tub & firepit
description:
Private piece of paradise makes a romantic getaway for a couple!
Wall of windows with garden door opening to large wrap around deck on the water- just for you!
Enjoy your private hot tub next to one of the gardens doors allowing you to open the door with the hot tub right there!
Wrap yourself in blankets and sit by the propane firepit (works like a bbq) with your morning coffee or evening drink.

The studio is spacious with queen size bed, remote allows you to control head and foot of the bed.
neighborhood_overview:
Very private area with a beautiful view.

Great place to use a base to visit all the local festivals and communities, including famous
St. Andrews by the Sea, only 20 min. away!

Walking distance to the 350 acre Ganong Nature Park, approximately 10 min.


SEAWINDS is located at the estuary where the sea waters of the Bay of Fundy meet the St. Croix River.
You will enjoy viewing the 38 foot tides coming and going from your private deck.
Twice a day, 160 billion tons of seawater is pulled into the world famous Bay of Fundy.
More than 4 times the combined flow of fresh water rivers on the planet is forced into a tighter and shallower area as the bay narrows.

You can use the private stairway that takes you to the beach and walk the ocean floor at low tide!

Many excellent choices from Picaroons Pub to gourmet, fine dining!

As a special courtesy to my guests, reservations have been made every Saturday
host_about:
This beautiful self- contained studio can be your hideaway when it is closed as a yoga studio.
If the weather allows you can inquire about a private yoga class on the 16'x36' deck.
Private entrance, closet, bathroom with shower. One large room with a wall of windows/garden door onto the deck overlooking the historic St. Croix River, which serves as an international boundary. 
Furnished with table and chairs,  leather couch, coffee table, table that can be used as a desk, makeup table with 20X magnification mirror, Wi-Fi, 4 K TV with satellite, DVD player, mini fridge, microwave, Kureig, queen size bed with remote to raise/lower foot of bed, new mattress topped with 4" memory foam!
You will enjoy the spectacular view of the  US coastline, including famous St Croix Island where the first settlers, led by Samuel de Champlain landed in 1604.
You are 20 minutes from the No. 1 rated destination in Canada, St. Andrews by the Sea!
If you like seafood, as much as I do, I can share the best places to buy fresh!

This area is known for great dining, including one of Canada's top 10 restaurants, Rossmount!

Please  note:
Be ready to chill this is a... 
NO STRESS ZONE  :)

name: Heaven Grand Falls NB
description:
Make memories at this unique family-friendly retreat.
The property was known as ‘the old fish hatchery. Much of its’ remains still exist; from the top of Mary”s Fall that flows into the St John River or at one time the cement pools. The fish house still stand but much more info is needed .
The home however has been renovated to include all todays modern amenities.
Come experience the magical powers of Mary’s Fall., you won’t want to leave!
host_about:
I enjoy meeting people and sharing my home town’s  natural beauty and it’s citizen who keep it safe and clean. 

I returned home after spending 40 years in Nova Scotia raising my family. 

We are blessed in Atlantic Canada with such a diverse landscape within  a small section of Canada. 

Being of Keltic  descent, I love to tell stories with lots of passion! Never let the truth get in the way of a good story  they say……….

host_about:
I love travel! Whether I'm traveling myself or making it possible for people to stay in my community it's all so important. When you travel you want to experience a place like a local...or at least I do. So for me, Airbnb is how it makes sense.
